# AEDIFICIUM — Project Overview

**Brand:** Execution infrastructure for professional design (architects & interior designers)
**Goal:** Rebuild existing WordPress site in Next.js 15 — same visual design, stable modern foundation
**Language:** English only (all UI copy and content)
**Repo:** https://github.com/zynaidev/aedificium_web
**Local dev:** localhost:3000 (no domain yet — VPS/Coolify deploy is final step)
**OS:** Windows PowerShell — use `Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .next` instead of `rm -rf .next`; run commands one at a time, not chained with `&&`

**Full spec:** `.cursor/aedificium_project_instructions.md`

## Site structure

Single-page landing at `/` — sections in order: Header/Nav → Hero → The Problem → Manifesto → The Platform → What We Believe → Brand Marquee → Final CTA → Footer.

```
app/(marketing)/layout.tsx   — Header + Footer + SmoothScrollProvider
app/(marketing)/page.tsx     — all sections composed
app/globals.css              — design tokens, resets, keyframes
app/layout.tsx               — root layout, fonts, metadata
components/layout/           — Header, Footer
components/sections/         — Hero, TheProblem, Manifesto, ThePlatform, WhatWeBelieve, BrandMarquee, FinalCTA
components/animations/       — FadeIn, ScrollReveal, CountUp
components/providers/        — SmoothScrollProvider
components/ui/               — Button, SectionLabel, Container
public/images/hero/          — interior photos (placeholder → real later)
```

## Tech stack

- Next.js 15 App Router + TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui (new-york, dark forced)
- Framer Motion (mount, scroll reveals, header), GSAP + ScrollTrigger (sticky cards), Lenis (smooth scroll)
- **No** Three.js / React Three Fiber
- Dynamic import + `ssr: false` for heavy animation components
- Hero images: `priority`; below-fold: `loading="lazy"`; use `<Image>` with `sizes`
- `next.config.ts`: `output: 'standalone'` (Docker/VPS)

## Git workflow

`feat/[name]` branches from main → commit `feat:` / `fix:` / `style:` / `perf:` / `refactor:` → PR → merge → delete branch.
File renames: always `git mv` (case sensitivity for Linux deploy). Never rename via Windows Explorer.

## Lighthouse targets

Performance 90+, Accessibility/SEO/Best Practices 100. Common killers: missing hero `priority`, missing explicit Image dimensions, too much main-thread JS.

## Deploy (later)

Coolify on Hetzner: Dockerfile, port 3000, network alias `aedificium-web`, Caddy `aedificium.design` → reverse_proxy, DNS A → 204.168.146.182.
